Relevant security agencies are investigating Wednesday’s attack by unknown persons on the Federal Medical Centre (FMC), Lokoja, Kogi State, Presidential Task Force on COVID-19 Control Chairman Boss Mustapha, said on Thursday. Condemning the incident, Mustapha is the Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF), said: “The PTF has received with great concern, reports about the attack on the Federal Medical Centre, Lokoja, Kogi State by some hoodlums. The PTF is particularly distressed and regrets the trauma to which medical workers, patients and others who went on their legitimate businesses were subjected. “I wish to assure you that security agencies have been tasked with the responsibility for fishing out the criminal elements behind it and they will be brought to justice. We thank law abiding Nigerians for reporting the occurrence promptly.”